pe consisting of two or more vertices,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"specified as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D"},{"type":"text","text":" instances, and the line segments that"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"connect them. For example, you could use an polyline to represent a road or the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"path along which something moves.","type":"text"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNShapeCollection":{"fragments":[{"text":"MLNShapeCollection","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"MLNShapeCollection","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeCollection","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeCollection"},{"type":"text","text":" object represents a shape consisting of zero or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"distinct but related shapes that are instances of "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShape"},{"type":"text","text":". The constituent"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"shapes can be a mixture of different kinds of shapes."}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnshapecollection"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNShapeSource":{"fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNShapeSource"}],"title":"MLNShapeSource","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is a map content source that supplies vector shapes to be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"shown on the map. The shapes may be instances of "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShape","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShape","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or they may be defined by local or external"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"GeoJSON"},{"type":"text","text":" code. A shape source is added to an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNStyle","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object along with an "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNStyle","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object. The vector style"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"layer defines the appearance of any content supplied by the shape source. You"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can update a shape source by setting its "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"shape"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"URL"},{"type":"text","text":" property."}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnshapesource"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPolygon":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon"},{"type":"text","text":" object represents a closed shape consisting of four or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"vertices, specified as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D"},{"type":"text","text":" instances, and the edges that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"connect them. For example, you could use a polygon shape to represent a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"building, a lake, or an area you want to highlight."}],"title":"MLNPolygon","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpolygon","fragments":[{"text":"MLNPolygon","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNMultiPolygon":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon"},{"type":"text","text":" object represents a shape consisting of one or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"polygons that do not overlap. For example, you could use a multipolygon shape"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to represent the body of land that consists of an island surrounded by an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"atoll: the inner island would be one "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon"},{"type":"text","text":" object, while the surrounding"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"atoll would be another. You could also use a multipolygon shape to represent a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"group of disconnected but related buildings."}],"title":"MLNMultiPolygon","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnmultipolygon","fragments":[{"text":"MLNMultiPolygon","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNSymbolStyleLayer":{"fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNSymbolStyleLayer"}],"title":"MLNSymbolStyleLayer","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNSymbolStyleLayer","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNSymbolStyleLayer","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is a style layer that renders icon and text labels"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"at points or along lines on the map."}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnsymbolstylelayer"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","title":"MapLibre","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","kind":"symbol","role":"collection"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNVectorStyleLayer":{"fragments":[{"text":"MLNVectorStyleLayer","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"MLNVectorStyleLayer","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNVectorStyleLayer","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNVectorStyleLayer"},{"type":"text","text":" is an abstract superclass for style layers whose content"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is defined by an "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource"},{"type":"text","text":" object."}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnvectorstylelayer"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNMapViewDelegate/mapView:imageForAnnotation:":{"fragments":[{"kind":"text","text":"- "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"mapView:imageForAnnotation:"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns an annotation image object to mark the given point annotation object on"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the map."}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnmapviewdelegate\/mapview:imageforannotation:","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapViewDelegate\/mapView:imageForAnnotation:","role":"symbol","title":"mapView:imageForAnnotation:","kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNMapView/addAnnotation:":{"fragments":[{"text":"- ","kind":"text"},{"text":"addAnnotation:","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Adds an annotation to the map view."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/addAnnotation:","title":"addAnnotation:","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnmapview\/addannotation:"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS/GeoJSON":{"role":"article","type":"topic","kind":"article","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/GeoJSON","title":"Working with GeoJSON Data","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre-native-for-ios\/geojson"}}}